# Design SV Licensing Policy  
### Protecting the Design SV Brand, Identity, and Creative Assets

The Design SV brand, along with all associated creative works, visual systems,
UI/UX patterns, animations, and presentation styles, constitutes proprietary
intellectual property owned exclusively by Design SV.

While the underlying source code in this repository may be licensed under the
MIT License, **the Design SV identity itself is not open-source**.

## Protected Creative Elements

The following categories are strictly protected and fall under **All Rights Reserved**:

- The “Soft Clay UI” visual language uniquely developed by Design SV  
- Custom animations, micro-interactions, transitions, and 3D effects  
- Custom-designed components, layouts, and section compositions  
- Color schemes, typography systems, layout DNA, and design philosophy  
- Any assets displayed in previews, demos, or project showcases  
- All 3D elements, story builder assets, and VR/AR interface designs  
- Project structures intended as part of the Design SV brand portfolio  

## Restrictions

You may **not**:

- Reuse Design SV brand elements in your own branding  
- Replicate the portfolio layout or design identity  
- Redistribute creative assets in any form  
- Use Design SV UI/UX designs commercially  
- Present derivative work as your own  
- Use the Design SV name, style, or visuals in advertising  
- Train AI models on Design SV assets or designs  
- Sell products based on Design SV creative work  

## Permitted Use

You **may**:

- Use the MIT-licensed code for personal or commercial development  
- Study the design approach for learning and inspiration  
- Fork code for development purposes (not the brand assets)  
- Reference the Design SV portfolio with proper attribution  

